          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Peng Tao",
          "email": "tao.peng@emc.com",
          "date": "2012-06-14 06:10:22.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Peng Tao",
          "email": "bergwolf@gmail.com",
          "date": "2012-07-16 10:29:07.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1113 llite: hide DCACHE_LUSTRE_INVALID in ll_dentry_data",
        "message": "LU-1113 llite: hide DCACHE_LUSTRE_INVALID in ll_dentry_data\n\nDCACHE_LUSTRE_INVALID is lustre private flag in vfs layer.\nReplace it with dentry->d_fsdata->lld_invalid so that it won't\nconflict with VFS flags.\n\nAfter dcache scalability patch, dentry->d_fsdata is always set\nbefore dentry is materised/rehashed. So if a dentry's d_fsdata\nis not set, then it is not hashed/materised. The patch make use\nof the fact and treat such dentry as invalid as well. It is\nnecessary because d_lustre_invalidate() can be called in\nll_invalidate_negative_children() and finds unmaterised/unhashed\ndentries.\n\nAlso drop all vfs_races patches as they are no longer needed.\n\nPlus two minor cleanups.\n\nSigned-off-by: Peng Tao <tao.peng@emc.com>\nChange-Id: I655154b8807440c99574ad6b865bd550cbc145f1\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
